The New Zealand medical devices market is characterized by intense competition, with key players focusing on product innovation, strategic partnerships, and mergers & acquisitions to strengthen their market position. Major players in the market include Fisher & Paykel Healthcare, ResMed, Medtronic, Philips Healthcare, and Siemens Healthineers. These companies are investing in research and development to introduce advanced medical devices that cater to the evolving needs of the healthcare industry. The increasing demand for digital health technologies and the growing focus on personalized medicine are expected to drive the market's growth in the coming years.

